gomodel:SYNGO_1795  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Immuno-electron micrographs demonstrated that Drp1, although clearly localized in part to mitochondria was also co-localized with clathrin at clathrin-coated pits in neurons fixed just after stimulation.\n\n17/11/2017 Pim\n- I have approved annotation to the 'endocytic zone' because high resolution data is presented that shows localization to clathrin coated pits at the presynaptic plasma membrane.\n- I have removed the 'extrinsic component of ...' element of the selected term because the mode of membrane interaction was not addressed in the presented data.. Experimental description: From the methods, \"Primary rat hippocampal neurons were prepared as described previously...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7806-5662" ;
        dc:date           "2017-11-15" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1795" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

